<HEAD>LaserPhoto NY14</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Model Jerry Hall says boyfriend Mick Jagger is
helping her prepare for her stage debut as Cherie in ``Bus Stop,''
the role Marilyn Monroe made famous in the 1956 film.
   In the play, Cherie, a dim Southern chanteuse, falls for Bo, a
yearning yokel.
   Jagger is helping Hall learn her lines for the production, which
opens July 26 at Montclair (N.J.) State College's Theatre Fest, she
told People magazine.
   ``He's got the Southern accent down pretty good,'' the Texas
native said of the British-born Rolling Stones singer.
   Hall said she will have no problem playing a dimwit.
   ``I have years of experience acting dumb,'' she said. ``In
