<FILEID>AP-NR-07-04-88 0520EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     07-04 0360</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0369</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Thunderstorms Ease Over Much Of The Nation</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Thunderstorms bore down on Montana today, pelting it with hail
and whipping up winds up 64 mph as much of the nation enjoyed mild
weather on the Fourth of July.
   Powerful thunderstorms were scattered across west central
Montana. The storms dropped hail an inch in diameter and generated
winds gusting to 53 mph in Helena late Sunday. In Great Falls,
winds roared up to 64 mph. Darby also got one-inch hail.
   Thunderstorms were widespread Sunday evening in the warm and
humid air of the Gulf Coast, but only isolated showers continued
into the morning.
   Today's forecast called for scattered showers and thunderstorms
from South Carolina to the Tennessee Valley and from Florida to
Louisiana; numerous showers and thunderstorms from Alabama to
Florida; widely scattered showers and thunderstorms from Texas to
southern Oklahoma, the Rocky Mountain states and northeast
California; and widely scattered showers through the Pacific
Northwest.
   High temperatures were forecast in the 80s or 90s across most of
the nation; around 100 degrees over western portions of the
northern and central Plains; over 110 degrees in parts of the
desert Southwest; and in the 60s and 70s in the Pacific Northwest
and along the California coast.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 46
degrees at Olympia, Wash., to 95 degrees at Phoenix, Ariz.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 70 drizzle; Boston 68 fair; Buffalo 61 partly
cloudy; Charleston, S.C. 71 cloudy; Cincinnati 67 fair; Cleveland
64 fair; Detroit 67 fair; Miami 80 fair; New York 67 fair;
Philadelphia 69 fair; Pittsburgh 66 fair; Portland, Maine 59 fair;
Washington 71 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 72 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth 78 fair; Denver 76
partly cloudy; Des Moines 69 fair; Indianapolis 72 fair; Kansas
City 71 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 71 fair; Nashville 74 hazy; New
Orleans 75 fair; St. Louis 73 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 74 partly cloudy; Anchorage 58 fair; Las
Vegas 91 windy; Los Angeles 63 cloudy; Phoenix 95 fair; Salt Lake
City 81 cloudy; San Diego 63 cloudy; San Francisco 56 cloudy;
Seattle 58 cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 63 fair; Toronto 64 partly cloudy.
