<HEAD>Military Conducts War Games</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The navy and air force battled each other in a
simulated nuclear and chemical war designed to test defense
capabilities, it was reported Monday.
   The two-hour mock battle was held late last month at an
undisclosed naval base in the East China Sea, the official People's
Daily said in its overseas edition.
   It did not say how many troops were involved in the exercise,
which began with the detonation of a simulated nuclear explosion.
Air force bombers then made simulated nuclear and chemical attacks
on the navy base, the newspaper said.
   It said the East Sea Fleet and base artillery units ``organized
effective firepower to counterattack'' and took protective action
against the radioactivity and chemicals, but it did not elaborate.
   China exploded its first atomic device in 1964 in the desert in
remote Xinjiang. It tested its first hydrogen bomb three years
later.
   It is believed to have half a dozen intercontinental ballistic
missiles with nuclear warheads and more than 100 medium-range
nuclear missiles.
