<HEAD>Police Investigate if Smugglers Drowned in Lake</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DAR ES SALAAM, Tanzania (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police are investigating whether
two boats carrying smugglers sank in Lake Tanganyika during storms
last week.
   ``We have been investigating the story for a week now, but there
is no clue yet on the reported sea accidents,'' Kigoma regional
police commander Fadhili Walele said Sunday in an interview with
the official Tanzanian news agency Shihata.
   Police had not found any bodies or wreckage from two boats
reported sunk in two separate storms on June 26 and June 30, he
said. Nor had they traced three people that witnesses said survived
one of the sinkings, he added.
   Police earlier said the boats were believed to have been
smuggling goods from Tanzania to Burundi or Zaire.
   Violent storms often strike Lake Tanganyika without warning,
capsizing small boats.
