<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF--NevadaQuake     07-04 0154</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Nevada Quake,0157</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Small Quake Proves to Be Rude Awakening to Boulder City Residents</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOULDER CITY, Nev. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A mild earthquake roused residents
early Monday, but there were no reports of damage or injury.
   The temblor struck at 3:57 a.m. and measured 3.7 on the Richter
scale of ground motion, said Russell Needham of the National
Earthquake Center in Golden, Colo. It was followed nearly two hours
later by a mild aftershock.
   The epicenter was 10 miles southwest of the city, which lies 30
miles southeast of Las Vegas, Needham said.
   Boulder City police reported numerous calls from residents from
as far away as Green Valley and Henderson, 20 miles to the north,
said dispatcher Nancy Shapiro.
   ``It woke me up out of a sound sleep and definitely startled
me,'' she said.
   An earthquake of 3.5 to 4 on the Richter scale could break
dishes in the immediate vicinity of the epicenter.
</TEXT>
