<1ST_LINE>r i AM-China-Storms     07-04 0126</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-China-Storms,0131</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Storms and Flooding Kill 65 In Sichuan Province</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONG KONG (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Storms and flooding have killed 65 people and
injured 1,420 others in China's southwestern Sichuan province, it
was reported Monday.
   In a broadcast monitored in Hong Kong, Beijing's official Xinhua
News Agency said the flooding took place in 36 counties late last
month.
   Provincial officials quoted the agency as saying 1,341 head of
livestock, 358,891 acres of crops, 100 small hydroelectric stations
and thousands of houses were destroyed,
   The agency said that officials estimated the loss at about $76
million.
   According to Xin Hua, the flooding forced schools, shops and
factories to shut down.
   Provincial government officials and rescue workers were rushed
to the devastated areas to carry out relief operations.
</TEXT>
