<HEAD>Four Members of Family Die in Duplex Fire</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Leads with 4 grafs to UPDATE with death of child. Picks up
4th graf pvs ``the family...''</NOTE>
<DATELINE>CANTON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fire swept through a duplex Monday, killing
five members of one family, fire officials said.
   Jack Blose, 35; his wife, Deborah, 31; their 12-year-old son
Jack Jr., and 5-year-old daughter, Rachel, were killed in the
blaze, the Stark County coroner's office said.
   Another daughter, Lacey, 4, died later at Akron Children's
Hospital, a spokeswoman there said.
   The causes of death had not been determined, pending a coroner's
report.
   The family rented one side of the duplex and the other side was
vacant, said Gary Kimble, an assistant chief for the Canton Fire
Department.
   The fire, which began on the front porch of the duplex, was
reported about 2:15 a.m., Kimble said. The fire caused about
$47,000 damage, he said.
   The cause of the fire was under investigation, Kimble said.
