<2ND_LINE>AM-Bodies Found,0210</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Mother Accused of Murdering Two Children</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WEST MEMPHIS, Ark. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two children whose burned bodies were
found near a dump were killed by their mother and another woman,
authorities charged Monday.
   Barbara McCoy, 40, the mother of the two children, and Mary
Delois Williams, 32, were in jail without bond Monday pending a
hearing Wednesday morning, Crittenden County Sheriff's investigator
Charles Walker said.
   Ms. McCoy, who is unemployed, and Ms. Williams, a teacher's
assistant, were arrested Monday at the Motel 6 in West Memphis,
where the two had apparently been staying for several days,
investigators said. Both were charged with first-degree murder.
   Walker and investigator R.D. Clay said authorities were alerted
by a man who found the bodies of Bianca Tirado, 7, and Maximillion
E. McCoy, 2, in plastic garbage bags just off a gravel road leading
to a dump between West Memphis and the Mississippi River.
   The children had been burned over 75 percent of their bodies,
Walker and Clay said.
   Walker said he suspects that the bodies were dumped Saturday
night or early Sunday morning.
   The children were slain elsewhere and dumped and set afire, Clay
said.
   Walker said an autopsy would probably be performed Tuesday
morning.
</TEXT>
